---
---

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
      <div class="badge-container mb-3" style="display: inline-block; background-color: rgba(82, 206, 199, 0.12); border-radius: 50px; padding: 0.35rem 1.25rem; border: 1px solid rgba(82, 206, 199, 0.25);">
        <span style="font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; color: #52CEC7; text-transform: uppercase;">Got Questions?</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h1 text-white">Startups Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-accordion">
      <!-- Question 1 -->
      <details class="faq-item" open>
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Why not hire freelancers?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Freelancers operate in silos, requiring you to act as the project manager, QA tester, and systems integrator. When you have a frontend dev, a backend dev, and a DevOps engineer working independently, code integrations break, timelines slip, and managing multiple contracts becomes a full-time job. Our pod is a pre-assembled, fully synchronized unit with a dedicated tech lead that handles delivery end-to-end.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 2 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Why not build an in-house team?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Building an in-house team is slow and capital-intensive. Sourcing, vetting, and onboarding 3–4 senior specialists takes 3 to 6 months and costs upwards of £25k/month in salaries, taxes, benefits, and recruitment agency fees. A pod lets you skip the hiring risk and launch development within 48 hours for a fraction of the cost, preserving your runway.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 3 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            How quickly can we start?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          We can kickoff within 48 hours of onboarding. Because our teams are already hired, vetted, and used to working together, there is no ramp-up time or notice period delays. We drop directly into your codebase and begin active development sprints immediately.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 4 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Can you work with our existing developers?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Absolutely. Our pods are modular and plug-and-play. Whether you have a sole developer or CTO who needs extra velocity, or a small existing team that lacks specialized DevOps or AI expertise, our engineers integrate seamlessly into your existing Git workflows, Slack channels, and agile sprints.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 5 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            What happens if we outgrow the pod?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Outgrowing us is the goal. We support you through your seed/pre-seed stages and build clean, well-documented codebases with automated CI/CD pipelines. When you secure your next funding round and are ready to hire a permanent in-house team, we manage a seamless hand-off and technical transition.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 6 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Are there long-term contracts?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          No. We operate on a rolling monthly subscription. We know startups need flexibility, so you can scale resources up or down, or cancel/pause the pod at any time with a simple 14-day notice—no lock-ins or strings attached.
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
